# Commit Analyzer Skill

Fetch recent commits from the repo and generate a human-readable summary.

## Steps
1. Fetch commits: GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/commits (limit: 10 default)
2. For each commit fetch the diff: GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/commits/{sha}
3. Group changes by: features added, bugs fixed, refactors, config/infra changes
4. Produce a structured summary:
   - One-line overview of what changed overall
   - Bulleted list grouped by category
   - Files most heavily changed
5. If a conventional commit format is detected, use it to improve grouping
